This bug description is a result of investigating JAVA-4155. The code
{code:java}
cursor.next(callback);
cachePostBatchResumeToken(cursor);
{code}
{code:java}
cursor.tryNext(callback);
cachePostBatchResumeToken(cursor);
{code}
in [{{AsyncChangeStreamBatchCursor.java}}|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-java-driver/blob/79cf2e586dcc1d49bc6b6ab423f19b884e6e8963/driver-core/src/main/com/mongodb/internal/operation/AsyncChangeStreamBatchCursor.java#L85] results in having a race condition: {{resumeToken}} may not yet be known [when retrying|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-java-driver/blob/79cf2e586dcc1d49bc6b6ab423f19b884e6e8963/driver-core/src/main/com/mongodb/internal/operation/AsyncChangeStreamBatchCursor.java#L260] the {{next}}/{{tryNext}} operation.

